  sodium: 1 g
  serving size: 560
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/pork-apple-burger-5f7f1e7a4a1941133f0f31cb
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: American
---

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pick the @rosemary{¼}(stalks) leaves from their stalks and finely
chop (discard the stalks).

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Lay on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle
over a little oil and sprinkle on the rosemary. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat,
then spread out evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

Coarsely grate the @apple{1}(deseeded and coarsely grated) (discard the core), no need to peel.
Place in a clean #tea towel{} and squeeze out as much juice as you can (you don't want soggy
burgers!). Put the @British pork mince{240%g} in a #mixing bowl{} and add the grated apple and
the @panko breadcrumbs{10}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well and form into
burgers 2cm thick (one per person).

> IMPORTANT! Wash your hands after touching raw meat!

Heat a glug of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, gently add the burgers and cook
them ~{5-6%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> Tip: Don't turn each burger until it has formed a crust on the underside or it might stick
to the pan!

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Once the burgers are cooked, take the pan
off the heat. Divide the cheese between the tops of the burgers, then pop a #lid{} on the pan
and set aside for the cheese to melt, about ~{4%minutes}.

While the burgers are cooking, slice each @burger buns{2} in half. Place on another baking
tray and pop them on the middle shelf of your oven to warm through for the last ~{2-3%minutes}
of potato cooking time.

> Tip: Watch your buns don't burn!

Put the @sugar{1} in another mixing bowl and add a squeeze of @lemon{½}(juiced) and
@olive oil{2}(tbsp). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Just before serving, add the
@wild rocket{40%g} and toss well.

Spread a little of the @apple and sage jelly{1} on the base of each burger bun. Serve your
burgers in the buns with some wedges and salad alongside. Enjoy!